  "text": "Importantly for consideration of the process of transplacental transmission, virus was detected in the blood of maternal mice (Table 4) . We anticipate that blood would be the likely route of infection in utero. Although it has been reported that MuPyV is rarely detected in the blood of infected normal adult animals [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , the sensitive RQ-PCR assay revealed viral presence in blood soon after infection. It is likely that the chance of transplacental transmission is related to the occurrence of an acute viral infection.",
